00237 /*
00238  * Get the probe set type.
00239  */
00240 affxcdf::GeneChipQCProbeSetType FusionCDFQCProbeSetInformation::GetQCProbeSetType() const
00241 {
00242         if (gcosSet)
00243                 return gcosSet->GetQCProbeSetType();
00244         else if (calvinSet)
00245         {
00246                 affxcdf::GeneChipQCProbeSetType qcType=affxcdf::UnknownQCProbeSetType;
00247                 const std::wstring &qc = calvinSet->GetQCProbeSetType();
00248                 for (int i=(int)affxcdf::UnknownQCProbeSetType; i<=(int)affxcdf::SpatialNormalizationPositiveQCProbeSetType; i++)
00249                 {
00250                         if (qc == FusionCDFQCProbeSetNames::GetStaticCDFQCProbeSetName((affxcdf::GeneChipQCProbeSetType)i))
00251                         {
00252                                 qcType = (affxcdf::GeneChipQCProbeSetType)i;
00253                                 break;
00254                         }
00255                 }
00256                 return qcType;
00257         }
00258         else
00259                 return affxcdf::UnknownQCProbeSetType;
00260 }

00488 /*
00489  * Get the groups direction.
00490  */
00491 affxcdf::DirectionType FusionCDFProbeGroupInformation::GetDirection() const
00492 {
00493         if (gcosGroup)
00494                 return gcosGroup->GetDirection();
00495         else if (calvinGroup)
00496         {
00497                 DirectionType dir = calvinGroup->GetDirection();
00498                 switch (dir)
00499                 {
00500                 case ProbeNoDirection:
00501                         return affxcdf::NoDirection;
00502                         break;
00503 
00504                 case ProbeSenseDirection:
00505                         return affxcdf::SenseDirection;
00506                         break;
00507 
00508                 case ProbeAntiSenseDirection:
00509                         return affxcdf::AntiSenseDirection;
00510                         break;
00511 
00512                 case ProbeEitherDirection:
00513                         return affxcdf::EitherDirection;
00514                         break;
00515 
00516                 default:
00517                         return affxcdf::NoDirection;
00518                         break;
00519                 }
00520         }
00521         else
00522                 return affxcdf::NoDirection;
00523 }

00722 /*
00723  * Gets the probe set type.
00724  */
00725 affxcdf::GeneChipProbeSetType FusionCDFProbeSetInformation::GetProbeSetType()
00726 {
00727         if (gcosSet)
00728                 return gcosSet->GetProbeSetType();
00729         else  if (calvinSet)
00730         {
00731                 CDFDataTypeIds psType = calvinSet->GetProbeSetType();
00732                 switch (psType)
00733                 {
00734                 case Expression:
00735                         return affxcdf::ExpressionProbeSetType;
00736                         break;
00737                         
00738                 case Genotyping:
00739                         return affxcdf::GenotypingProbeSetType;
00740                         break;
00741 
00742                 case Tag:
00743                         return affxcdf::TagProbeSetType;
00744                         break;
00745 
00746                 case Resequencing:
00747                         return affxcdf::ResequencingProbeSetType;
00748                         break;
00749 
00750         case CopyNumber:
00751             return affxcdf::CopyNumberProbeSetType;
00752             break;
00753 
00754         case GenotypeControl:
00755             return affxcdf::GenotypeControlProbeSetType;
00756             break;
00757 
00758         case ExpressionControl:
00759             return affxcdf::ExpressionControlProbeSetType;
00760             break;
00761 
00762                 default:
00763                         return affxcdf::UnknownProbeSetType;
00764                         break;
00765                 }
00766         }
00767         else
00768                 return affxcdf::UnknownProbeSetType;
00769 }

00978 /*
00979  * Get the chip type (probe array type) of the CDF file.
00980  * This is the name of the file without extension.
00981  */
00982 std::string FusionCDFData::GetChipType() const
00983 {
00984         int index = (int) fileName.rfind('\\');
00985         if (index == -1)
00986                 index = (int) fileName.rfind('/');
00987         std::string chiptype = fileName.c_str() + index + 1;
00988         chiptype.resize(chiptype.length()-4);
00989         return chiptype;
00990 }
00991 
00992 /*
00993  * Get the chip type (probe array type) of the CDF file.
00994  * This is the name of the file without extension. We
00995  * also include all substrings create by removing
00996  * characters to the right of each '.'
00997  */
00998 std::vector<std::string> FusionCDFData::GetChipTypes() const
00999 {
01000     std::vector<std::string> chiptypes;
01001     std::string chiptype;
01002 
01003         int index = (int) fileName.rfind('\\');
01004         if (index == -1)
01005                 index = (int) fileName.rfind('/');
01006         chiptype = fileName.c_str() + index + 1;
01007         chiptype.resize(chiptype.length()-4);
01008 
01009     // The full file name (minus .cdf extension) is the default (1st) 
01010     // chip type. This matches what GetChipType() returns.
01011     // ie: foo.bar.v1.r2.cdf -> foo.bar.v1.r2
01012     chiptypes.push_back(chiptype);
01013 
01014     //We then add all substrings starting at zero and ending at '.'
01015     // ie: foo.bar.v1.r2.cdf -> foo.bar.v1, foo.bar, foo
01016     std::string::size_type pos = chiptype.rfind(".",chiptype.size()-1);
01017     while (pos != std::string::npos){
01018         if(pos>0)
01019             chiptypes.push_back(chiptype.substr(0,pos));
01020         pos = chiptype.rfind(".",pos-1);
01021     }
01022 
01023     //ie: foo.bar.v1.r2, foo.bar.v1, foo.bar, foo
01024         return chiptypes;
01025 }

01027 /*
01028  * Read the entire file.
01029  */
01030 bool FusionCDFData::Read()
01031 {
01032         CreateObject();
01033         if (gcosData)
01034         {
01035                 gcosData->SetFileName(fileName.c_str());
01036                 return gcosData->Read();
01037         }
01038         else
01039         {
01040                 CDFFileReader reader;
01041                 reader.SetFilename(fileName);
01042                 try
01043                 {
01044                         reader.Read(*calvinData);
01045                 }
01046                 catch(...)
01047                 {
01048                         return false;
01049                 }
01050                 return true;
01051         }
01052 }

01116 /*
01117  * Determines if a CDF file is of the Calvin format.
01118  */
01119 bool FusionCDFData::IsCalvinCompatibleFile(const char *fileName)
01120 {
01121         GenericData data;
01122         GenericFileReader reader;
01123         reader.SetFilename(fileName);
01124         try
01125         {
01126                 reader.ReadHeader(data, GenericFileReader::ReadNoDataGroupHeader);
01127                 return true;
01128         }
01129         catch (affymetrix_calvin_exceptions::CalvinException)
01130         {
01131         }
01132         return false;
01133 }

01135 /*
01136  * Get the probe set type for non-qc probe sets.
01137  */
01138 affxcdf::GeneChipProbeSetType FusionCDFData::GetProbeSetType(int index) const
01139 {
01140         if (gcosData)
01141         {
01142                 return gcosData->GetProbeSetType(index);
01143         }
01144         else if (calvinData && calvinData->GetGenericData().Header().GetGenericDataHdr()->GetFileTypeId() != AFFY_CNTRL_PS)
01145         {
01146                 std::string dataTypeId = calvinData->GetDataTypeId();
01147                 if (dataTypeId == AFFY_EXPR_PS)
01148                         return affxcdf::ExpressionProbeSetType;
01149 
01150                 else if (dataTypeId == AFFY_GENO_PS)
01151                         return affxcdf::GenotypingProbeSetType;
01152 
01153                 else if (dataTypeId == AFFY_RESEQ_PS)
01154                         return affxcdf::ResequencingProbeSetType;
01155 
01156                 else if (dataTypeId == AFFY_TAG_PS)
01157                         return affxcdf::TagProbeSetType;
01158 
01159                 else
01160                         return affxcdf::UnknownProbeSetType;
01161         }
01162         else
01163                 return affxcdf::UnknownProbeSetType;
01164 }
